## Limitations
The findings are based on available literature and may not encompass all aspects of the relationship between emotional states and menstrual cycles. The complexity of individual hormonal and emotional responses means that results can vary widely among women. Additionally, some sources may not be peer-reviewed, which could affect the reliability of the information. Further research, particularly longitudinal studies, would be beneficial to deepen the understanding of this relationship.

